The defendant Dewal R Barnes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dewal R Barnes in court with attorney Gary Edward Rosenthal.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

The Court ordered defendant to serve 7 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 30 days time served, STRAIGHT TIME. 

Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs, fees and surcharges (including DNA surcharge) by 2/8/2019, or serve 10 days in the House of Correction.

Court objects to Electronic Monitoring.

Upon successful completion of the sentence Court will allow for expungement.
